pwd: present working directory
Purpose: shows the full path of the current directory.
example:
renuka@Bunny:~$ whoami
renuka
renuka@Bunny:~$ pwd
/home/renuka
-----------------------------
ls >> Only visible files/folders, no sizes
renuka@Bunny:~$ ls
c1.txt  c2.txt  c3.txt
-------------------------------
ls -l : Long format with sizes in bytes
renuka@Bunny:~$ ls -l
total 12
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 1024 Oct 25 06:09 c1.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 2048 Oct 25 06:09 c2.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 3072 Oct 25 06:09 c3.txt
-----------------------------------------------------
ls -lh >> Long format with human-readable sizes, no hidden files
renuka@Bunny:~$ ls -lh
total 12K
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 1.0K Oct 25 06:09 c1.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 2.0K Oct 25 06:09 c2.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 renuka renuka 3.0K Oct 25 06:09 c3.txt
---------------------------------------------------------
